\par "How much?" I asked when he closed the book.
\par "Four-seventy."
\par "A triple," I said.
\par He shrugged and said, "Not bad."
\par Five hundred pounds equaled a home run, something he accom\-plished every other day. He squatted and said, "Hop on."
