\par "Leon Spruill," he said with food on his lip. "Nice to meet you."
\par "Happy to have you folks here," my father said pleasantly.
\par "Thank you," Mr. Spruill said, pulling up his pants. "This here is my wife, Lucy." She smiled and kept chewing slowly.
\par "This is my daughter, Tally," he said, pointing. When she looked at me, I could feel my cheeks burning.
\par "And these are my nephews, Bo and Dale," he said, nodding to the two boys who'd been resting on the mattress when they had stopped on the highway. They were teenagers, probably fifteen or so. And sit\-
ting next to them was the giant I'd first seen on the tailgate, half-asleep.
