\par He paused for a split second as if he really wanted me to respond. I was tempted to run away, but I just stared at my boots. The rest of the Spruills may have felt sorry for me, but none of them came to my rescue.
\par "We got a house nicer than yours, boy. You believe that? A lot nicer."
\par "Quiet down, Hank," Mrs. Spruill said.
\par "It's bigger, got a long front porch, got a tin roof without tar patches, and you know what else it's got? You ain't gonna believe this, boy, but our house's got paint on it. White paint. You ever see paint, boy?"
