\par "Scared of what?"
\par "Scared of gettin' caught behind the Co-op watchin' a fight."
\par "Because I told you not to, right?" asked my mother.
\par "Yes ma'am. And I'm sorry."
\par Watching a fight was not a major act of disobedience, and all three of us knew it. What were boys supposed to do on Saturday afternoon when the town was packed and excitement was high? She smiled be\-
cause I said I was sorry. I was trying to look as pitiful as possible.
\par "I'm not too worried about you watchin' a fight," my father said.
\par "But secrets can get you in trouble. You shoulda told me what you saw."
