\par Several of the Methodists asked me about Ricky\emdash how was he do\-ing, had we heard from him. I tried to be nice and answer their ques\-
tions, but as a family we Chandlers did not enjoy this attention. And now that we were horrified over the Latcher secret, any mention of Ricky in public scared us.
\par "Tell him we're thinkin' about him," they said. They always said this, as if we owned a phone and called him every night.
\par "We're prayin' for him," they said.
\par "Thank you," I always replied.
\par A perfectly wonderful moment like the Fall Picnic could be ruined wit
