\par "Who's Theodore?" I asked.
\par "One of the dispatchers. He sleeps half the time."
\par So do you, I thought to myself. "Can you turn on the siren?" I asked.
\par "Nope. It might scare your momma."
\par "What about the lights?"
\par "Nope, they burn up the battery." He reached for the ignition; the engine grunted and strained but wouldn't turn over.
