a striking contrast between new white and old pale brown. The project had to be finished.
\par Even my father seemed uneasy about the idea of parting with more cash, but he said to me, "You can go."
\par "I'll stay here," my mother said. "We need to put up some okra."
\par Another trip to town. I was a happy boy. No pressure to pick cot\-ton, nothing to do but ride down the highway and dream of somehow obtaining candy or ice cream once I arrived in Black Oak. I had to be careful, though, because I was the only happy Chandl
